I'm the source of this ugly pattern. Given an object whose serializable attributes all are `None`, the serializer outputs an empty object. So we'd send over the wire something like
```json
{
  "attributes": {}
}
```

`__new__` is run before `__init__`. The arguments would go to `__init__` as well. We just wouldn't have to do that ourselves. Details in [these docs]( https://docs.python.org/3/reference/datamodel.html#object.__new__ ).

