> One issue I have lately is that when I iterate ip6 addresses of a Child, I have to copy each address to a local variable, which is less efficient than ideal. For example, I wanted to iterate only multicast addresses, but all addresses including MlEID were copied. If we want to implement a iteration over a subset of Child addresses without copying other addresses, which pattern can better support it?

@simonlingoogle , the reason for copying (as you probably noticed) is that we don't save the full mesh-local address and we just save the IID portion and we would need to create it in address instance provided by caller. The optimization for saving only IID of mesh-local address was mainly to reduce RAM, (since we can have many children any reduction in info per child,  can add up).

I have been planning to simplify the `Child:GetNextIp6Address` and related `Iterator` code. Will think of this (and how to add a filtering model so we can get only multicast or unicast addresses).

